  "sphere_commentary": {
    "run_date": "2026-04-11",
    "overview": "The aggregate data shows positive listener responses across protocols, with HEALING series leading in consistency, THRIVING in mean scores, and TRANSFORMING exhibiting expected variability.\n• HEALING protocols (n=574) maintain strong consistency (mean 6.98, std 1.77), particularly DESCENT types for anxiety and sleep.\n• THRIVING series (n=245) matches HEALING's mean (6.96) with standout Focus & Clarity protocols (T-FC-L3: 7.63).\n• TRANSFORMING (n=181) shows widest variance (std 1.87) and lower mean (6.59), aligning with its ascending design for low-affect states.\n• YouTube reach and retention data is largely incomplete, limiting engagement correlation analysis.",
    "cross_series": "The three series demonstrate distinct performance profiles.\n• HEALING protocols cluster closely around design intent, delivering 6.9–7.1 means across anxiety, crisis, and sleep contexts.\n• THRIVING's HOLD protocols achieve higher means (7.63 in T-FC-L3), indicating efficacy in focus optimization but with lower sample sizes.\n• TRANSFORMING ASCENT protocols show lower means (6.36–7.15) and higher variance, reflecting challenges in engaging listeners with ascending arcs for low-affect states.\n• DESCENT protocols across series outperform ASCENT types, suggesting entrainment differences between Hz parameter designs.",
    "anomalies": "Key anomalies identified across analyses.\n• X-MC-L3 (n=10, mean=5.7, std=2.45) — Lowest mean and highest variance signal potential design mismatch or population split [CONVERGENT].\n• H-CR-L1 (n=43, mean=6.35) underperforms HEALING series mean by 0.63 points, expected but worth reviewing crisis protocol calibration [CONVERGENT].\n• YouTube retention data is NULL across all protocols, hindering reach-efficacy correlation [CONVERGENT].\n• Significant cross-run drift in X-ME-L1 (sim=0.653) and others suggests evolving listener interpretations or analytical instability [CONVERGENT].",
    "development_signals": "Targeted development opportunities.\n• [CONVERGENT SIGNAL] X-MC-L3 — Investigate design parameters and population fit; create L2 variant with revised Hz range.\n• [CONVERGENT] H-CR-L1 — Test slower descent gradient or adviser-driven intro to improve crisis outcomes.\n• [CONVERGENT] X-ME-L1 — Reposition or create variant for cross-series use per AutoGluon's cross-bucket recommendation.\n• T-FC-L3 — Analyze design differentiation to replicate its high mean (7.63) in other protocols [SINGLE SOURCE].",
    "embedding_analysis": "Embedding analysis reveals patterns of analytical instability and semantic clustering.\n• CROSS-RUN DRIFT: 14 protocols show similarity <0.75 (e.g., X-ME-L1 at 0.653), suggesting evolving data patterns [CONVERGENT].\n• SEMANTIC CLUSTERS: HEALING anxiety protocols cluster tightly (H-AX-L2/L3 sim=0.846); X-MC-L3 is analytically distinct [CONVERGENT].\n• Confidence: Drift insights are provisional due to limited historical runs but suggest meaningful shifts in protocol framing.",
